<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-416-311  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 416 311.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  June 26 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>MCI introduces MCI Vision, long distance for small business. (MCICommunications Corp.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Blankenhorn, Dana.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   MCI Communications Corp. (communication systems).andO;Ticker:    MCIC.andO;Topic:     Telecommunications ServicesLong-Distance Telephone ServicesProduct IntroductionSmall Business.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>MCI INTRODUCES MCI VISION, LONG DISTANCE FOR SMALL BUSINESS WASHINGTON, D.C.,andO;U.S.A., 1990 JUN 20 (NB) -- MCI Communications unveiled a long distanceservice aimed at the $18 billion small business market called MCI Vision.andP;  Itis designed to provide features and capabilities previously available only tothe largest firms.andM;MCI Vision offers customers a menu of long distance features that can betailored to their business, new billing and management aids and broad volumediscounts based on combined long distance usage for all of a company'scalling -- all at prices based upon a flat per-minute rate, regardless of thedistance or volume of calls.andP;  The new service is targeted to customersspending between $500 and $50,000 monthly on long distance services.andM;MCI Vision permits customers to centralize and control company- wide longdistance usage by individual, department or location, and by the origin ordestination of the call.andP;  Customers receive a single, comprehensive invoiceand reporting package.andP;  The report package details long distance calls andcharges for outbound and credit card calls, for domestic and internationalcalls, and for all of a company's locations in an easy to read format.andP;  Callscan easily be identified by codes assigned to specific employees, departmentsor calling cards.andP;  Service begins in mid-July.andM;(Dana Blankenhorn/19900622/Press Contact: MCI Communications, Corporate NewsBureau, 800-289-0073)</TEXT></DOC>